This paper deals with image reconstruction using a machine learning framework, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of supervised learning also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data-driven methods, which could also place it under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of undersampled data, which could also make it relevant to the category of information theory (cs.IT).
